msgid "logs-istio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:4
msgid ""
"Monitoring is crucial to support transitioning to the microservices "
"architecture style. Other requirements include rapid provisioning and "
"rapid deployment, according to `this article "
"<https://aadrake.com/posts/2017-05-20-enough-with-the-"
"microservices.html>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:9
msgid ""
"With Istio, you gain monitoring of the traffic between microservices by "
"default. You can use the Istio Dashboard for monitoring your "
"microservices in real time."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:13
msgid ""
"Istio is integrated out-of-the-box with `Prometheus time series database "
"and monitoring system <https://prometheus.io>`_. Prometheus collects "
"various traffic-related metrics and provides `a rich query language "
"<https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/querying/basics/>`_ for "
"them."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:19
msgid "See below several examples of Prometheus Istio-related queries."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:21
msgid ""
"Access the Prometheus UI at http://my-istio-logs-database.io. (The ``my-"
"istio-logs-database.io`` URL should be in your /etc/hosts file, you set "
"it `previously </docs/examples/microservices-istio/bookinfo-kubernetes"
"/#update-your-etc-hosts-configuration-file>`_)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:31
msgid ""
"Run the following example queries in the *Expression* input box. Push the"
" *Execute* button to see query results in the *Console* tab. The queries "
"use ``tutorial`` as the name of the application’s namespace, substitute "
"it with the name of your namespace. For best results, run the real-time "
"traffic simulator described in the previous steps when querying data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:38
msgid "Get all the requests in your namespace:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:40
msgid ""
"{{< text plain >}} "
"istio_requests_total{destination_service_namespace=“tutorial”, "
"reporter=“destination”}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:44
msgid "Get the sum of all the requests in your namespace:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:46
msgid ""
"{{< text plain >}} "
"sum(istio_requests_total{destination_service_namespace=“tutorial”, "
"reporter=“destination”})"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:50
msgid "Get the requests to ``reviews`` microservice:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:52
msgid ""
"{{< text plain >}} "
"istio_requests_total{destination_service_namespace=“tutorial”, "
"reporter=“destination”,destination_service_name=“reviews”}"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:56
msgid ""
"`Rate "
"<https://prometheus.io/docs/prometheus/latest/querying/functions/#rate>`_"
" of requests over the past 5 minutes to all instances of the ``reviews`` "
"microservice:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:60
msgid ""
"{{< text plain >}} "
"rate(istio_requests_total{destination_service_namespace=“tutorial”, "
"reporter=“destination”,destination_service_name=“reviews”}[5m])"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/docs/examples/microservices-istio/logs-istio/index.rst:65
msgid ""
"The queries above use the ``istio_requests_total`` metric, which is a "
"standard Istio metric. You can observe other metrics, in particular, the "
"ones of Envoy (`Envoy <https://www.envoyproxy.io>`_ is the sidecar proxy "
"of Istio). You can see the collected metrics in the *insert metric at "
"cursor* drop-down menu."
msgstr ""

